I'm fine picking him up,
but you're welcome
to come over, too.

01:18.311 --> 01:19.845
Whatever you want.

01:19.879 --> 01:22.347
No. Whatever you want.
I'm fine with whatever you want.

01:22.382 --> 01:25.851
All right. Then maybe
you could drop him off,
if you don't mind.

01:25.885 --> 01:27.319
I don't mind.
But it's not a date.

01:27.353 --> 01:29.054
I think I'll just spend
some time with John tonight.

01:29.088 --> 01:31.056
All right.
See you later.

01:31.090 --> 01:33.091
But not for a date.

01:38.331 --> 01:40.999
Just, uh, tell her you're
not gonna marry her. Yeah.

01:41.033 --> 01:42.834
You're not gonna marry her.
I said, "We'll see."

01:42.869 --> 01:45.470
I'll think about it,
but I'm not getting married
while I'm in high school.

01:45.505 --> 01:47.739
What about in June?
You'll be graduating in June.

01:47.774 --> 01:49.141
No, not in June.

01:49.175 --> 01:50.909
July? Oh, August.

01:50.943 --> 01:52.477
[sighs]
Admit it.

01:52.512 --> 01:54.980
You're one step away from being
in the same boat I'm in.

01:55.014 --> 01:57.249
No, I'm not.
Find a condo yet?

01:57.283 --> 01:58.717
No, not yet.

01:58.751 --> 02:01.052
So the one
you looked at last night
didn't work out either?

02:01.087 --> 02:02.788
No. No. These things
take time, you know?

02:02.822 --> 02:04.723
We just started looking,
we're on a limited budget,

02:04.757 --> 02:06.725
so I doubt we'll buy anything
right away.

02:06.759 --> 02:08.627
Yeah, especially if
you're not ready to leave home.

02:08.661 --> 02:11.096
Who's not ready
to leave home at 17, huh?

02:11.130 --> 02:13.965
It's every teenager's dream
to get their own home at 17.

02:14.000 --> 02:15.634
Yeah, and a wife and a baby.

02:15.668 --> 02:17.469
You get your life
over with in your teen years,

02:17.503 --> 02:19.137
and then there's just
nothing else to do

02:19.172 --> 02:20.539
but kick back and watch

02:20.573 --> 02:22.574
every dream you ever had
go straight to hell.

02:22.608 --> 02:24.242
[chuckles]

02:24.277 --> 02:27.245
It's looking that way,
but it'll all be fine.

02:27.280 --> 02:29.414
Yeah. That's what
I keep saying to myself:

02:29.449 --> 02:31.249
"It'll all be fine."

02:31.284 --> 02:33.518
Yeah.

02:35.221 --> 02:37.989
I guess I'd wanna wait
until we both graduated
from high school.

02:38.024 --> 02:40.058
Then again,
he is graduating this year,

02:40.092 --> 02:42.060
and then I only have
a year left of high school.

02:42.094 --> 02:43.962
So whatever.
I'm not really in any hurry.

02:43.996 --> 02:45.997
I heard you asked Ricky
to marry you.

02:46.032 --> 02:47.666
Nice going, girlfriend.

02:47.700 --> 02:49.935
Good luck with that
nontraditional approach.

02:52.138 --> 02:54.139
Well, what was
his answer, exactly?

02:54.173 --> 02:55.640
He said he'd think
about it.

02:55.675 --> 02:58.176
No. He said, "We'll see."
It's a totally different thing.

02:58.211 --> 03:00.545
Well, it's different,
but it's not exactly a "yes."

03:00.580 --> 03:02.614
It's not a "no."
And coming from Ricky,

03:02.648 --> 03:04.115
I think it's a "yes."

03:04.150 --> 03:06.318
I mean, I didn't expect him
to say "yes" right away.

03:06.352 --> 03:07.819
He has to think about things,

03:07.854 --> 03:09.421
and he has to feel in control.

03:09.455 --> 03:12.190
And I'm definitely going
to let him feel in control
of his decision.

03:12.225 --> 03:13.725
I gotta say,
I'm impressed

03:13.759 --> 03:15.227
that you went out
on a limb, Amy,

03:15.261 --> 03:17.095
and just asked
for what you wanted.

03:17.129 --> 03:18.797
I think that's brave.

03:18.831 --> 03:21.199
Either brave
or completely foolish.

03:21.234 --> 03:23.301
Good morning.

03:23.336 --> 03:25.303
Obviously she didn't approve.

03:25.338 --> 03:27.305
Well, uh, how long
do you think

03:27.340 --> 03:29.341
it'll take Ricky to see
that he's gonna marry you?

03:29.375 --> 03:31.476
He needs time.

03:34.914 --> 03:36.248
Oh. Good morning.

03:36.282 --> 03:38.216
Did I know you were
coming by this morning?

03:38.251 --> 03:40.519
I don't know.
Here's my work.
See you next week.

03:40.553 --> 03:42.387
Oh. Whoa, whoa, whoa.
No, no, no.

03:42.421 --> 03:44.523
That's not how this works.

03:44.557 --> 03:46.925
We have to go over
your assignments.

03:46.959 --> 03:48.994
Not even we.

03:49.028 --> 03:51.897
The school has a new teacher
who's overseeing home schooling.

03:51.931 --> 03:54.399
Mr. Malkovich.
Let me go get him for you.

03:54.433 --> 03:56.401
I wish you had told me.

03:56.435 --> 03:58.670
My dad's waiting outside.

03:58.704 --> 04:00.338
I don't really have time.

04:00.373 --> 04:03.341
Yes. I'm sure you're
very busy at home.

04:06.712 --> 04:08.613
Hi, Angel.
Nadine, good morning.

04:08.648 --> 04:10.649
Jeff, what's up, man?

04:10.683 --> 04:12.918
Hey, uh, Ricky,
I need to talk to you.

04:12.952 --> 04:15.153
When you have time.

04:15.187 --> 04:17.188
What's that about?

04:17.223 --> 04:19.591
I don't know.
What does she do?
She's the counselor.

04:19.625 --> 04:21.259
No. I know
she's the counselor.

04:21.293 --> 04:22.694
What does she do?

04:22.728 --> 04:25.196
She counsels students
on school

04:25.231 --> 04:27.732
and what classes to take,
where to go to college.

04:27.767 --> 04:30.702
Stuff like that.
Yeah, well, I'm not
going to college.

04:30.736 --> 04:33.305
Yeah, well, you already
have a job and a family.
That's totally understandable.

04:33.339 --> 04:36.474
I'm glad you think so.

04:39.545 --> 04:41.112
I don't wanna
do it in my room

04:41.147 --> 04:43.248
'cause it's so close
to my mom and Jeff's,

04:43.282 --> 04:45.550
and they have no plans
to go anywhere for months.

04:45.585 --> 04:48.019
Mm-hmm.
There's always
the guest house,

04:48.054 --> 04:50.121
but then I'd have to strike
some sort of deal

04:50.156 --> 04:51.957
with Tom and Jack,

04:51.991 --> 04:53.959
and then
they'd know about it.

04:53.993 --> 04:55.961
I don't know.
It just doesn't feel right,
you know?

04:55.995 --> 04:58.563
To do what we wanna do
in Jack's bed.

04:58.598 --> 05:00.131
Hi, Adrian.
Hi.

05:00.166 --> 05:02.100
Would it be possible
to talk to you alone, Grace?

05:02.134 --> 05:03.568
Yeah, sure.

05:03.603 --> 05:05.503
But anything you wanna say,
you can say in front of Adrian.

05:05.538 --> 05:07.038
She's my best friend.

05:08.040 --> 05:09.708
Bye.

05:11.510 --> 05:14.412
My mom's going out of town
with my dad tonight,

05:14.447 --> 05:17.282
so we have my house
all to ourselves.

05:18.517 --> 05:20.051
We don't have to do anything.

05:20.086 --> 05:22.053
But if you wanna do something,

05:22.088 --> 05:23.788
we do have my house
all to ourselves.

05:24.991 --> 05:27.192
And it's okay with my parents
if you comover.

05:27.226 --> 05:28.893
It's even okay
if you spend the night.

05:28.928 --> 05:30.028
Your house?

05:31.163 --> 05:33.298
Your bed?

05:33.332 --> 05:35.300
I don't really know
if I feel comfortable with that.

05:35.334 --> 05:37.302
I've slept over at your house,
in your bed.

05:37.336 --> 05:39.170
Yeah...

05:39.205 --> 05:41.473
But I don't know.

05:47.947 --> 05:49.247
Good morning.

05:49.281 --> 05:51.249
Hey, look,
I'm sorry about last night.

05:51.283 --> 05:53.952
I guess I'm being just
a little picky about the condo.

05:54.954 --> 05:56.421
I guess you are.

05:56.455 --> 05:58.823
But that's okay.
We have more to look at tonight.

05:58.858 --> 06:01.393
Really?
Um, are you up for it?

06:01.427 --> 06:03.428
I mean, we've looked at places
every night this week.

06:03.462 --> 06:04.763
Maybe you should get some rest.

06:04.797 --> 06:06.731
Are you kidding?
Next to the baby,

06:06.766 --> 06:09.701
this is the most exciting thing
that's ever happened
to me in my life.

06:09.735 --> 06:11.236
Bye, Benny.

06:11.270 --> 06:12.937
Benny?

06:12.972 --> 06:14.272
Benny?

06:14.306 --> 06:16.941
I'm really okay
with that.

06:16.976 --> 06:17.976
Sure you are.

06:18.010 --> 06:19.144
I am.

06:19.178 --> 06:20.845
I've accepted my fate.

06:20.880 --> 06:22.681
Except for
the "moving out
of your house" part.

06:23.716 --> 06:25.817
Yeah, maybe not that.

