06:57.375 --> 06:59.476
My favorite.

06:59.510 --> 07:01.478
You have any friends?

07:01.512 --> 07:03.046
Yeah, I have friends.
Who?

07:03.080 --> 07:05.215
Well, that's kind of
personal information, isn't it?

07:05.249 --> 07:07.651
I mean, if I tell you,
you might post it
on the Internet.

07:07.685 --> 07:09.653
Never mind.
I already know.

07:09.687 --> 07:11.755
I talked to your father.

07:11.789 --> 07:13.457
He was right outside
in the car.

07:13.491 --> 07:16.026
Katelyn told me,
so I went out
and introduced myself.

07:17.328 --> 07:19.629
Did you, uh,

07:19.664 --> 07:21.465
<i>actually read Ulysses,</i>

07:21.499 --> 07:23.700
or did you just read
the study guide?

07:23.734 --> 07:26.369
Did you actually graduate
from college in education,

07:26.404 --> 07:27.971
or did you just read
the study guide?

07:28.005 --> 07:29.239
You missed a few things.

07:29.273 --> 07:30.540
Maybe you missed a few things.

07:30.575 --> 07:33.343
Probably.
Do you speed read?

07:33.377 --> 07:34.544
No.

07:34.579 --> 07:36.513
I learned to speed read
when I was your age.

07:36.547 --> 07:39.649
Loved it.
Very useful skill to have.

07:39.684 --> 07:42.385
Well, looks okay.

07:42.420 --> 07:44.221
But I'll take the weekend

07:44.255 --> 07:46.923
to, uh, delve into this
a little more deeply,

07:46.958 --> 07:49.359
and look over your other work.

07:50.928 --> 07:53.663
Do that, because I spent
a lot of time doing that work.

07:53.698 --> 07:55.665
Tell me a little
about yourself.

07:55.700 --> 07:58.568
I'd like to get you connected
with some of the other kids
doing home schooling.

07:58.603 --> 08:02.205
Well, about myself,

08:02.240 --> 08:04.875
I don't care to be connected
with any of the other kids

08:04.909 --> 08:06.810
doing home schooling.

08:06.844 --> 08:10.580
I'm connecting you.
You need to be connected.

08:10.615 --> 08:12.716
You can't just hide over
at your house

08:12.750 --> 08:15.151
without any social interaction

08:15.186 --> 08:17.053
with any other student
on the planet.

08:17.088 --> 08:18.154
Why not?

08:18.189 --> 08:20.090
Because that's what
your dad said.

08:20.124 --> 08:22.492
And what he said goes.
He also said that.

08:22.527 --> 08:24.594
And he said for me
to tell you that,

08:24.629 --> 08:27.364
which I guess means
that he couldn't tell you.

08:27.398 --> 08:28.899
Guess he's
a little overwhelmed.

08:28.933 --> 08:31.234
Well, that's not my problem.

08:32.470 --> 08:33.503
[horn honks]

08:33.538 --> 08:35.005
I can't take it.

08:35.039 --> 08:36.907
I don't have another adult
to talk to.

08:36.941 --> 08:39.543
Donovan calls from the store--
it's the highlight of my day.

08:39.577 --> 08:41.378
I need another adult
to talk to, Anne.

08:41.412 --> 08:42.611
Been there, done that.

08:42.647 --> 08:44.314
Yeah, but at least you had
someone to talk to

08:44.348 --> 08:46.316
when I came home at night.

08:46.350 --> 08:48.251
Yeah, okay.
I wasn't that adult.

08:48.286 --> 08:49.586
I gotta make some friends.

08:49.620 --> 08:51.154
You have friends.

08:51.188 --> 08:53.223
Why don't you call Ruben,
do something with him?

08:53.257 --> 08:54.891
'Cause he's a big,
important prosecutor,

08:54.926 --> 08:57.327
and I'm just a house man.

08:57.361 --> 08:58.628
That's ridiculous.

08:58.663 --> 08:59.763
No, it's not.

08:59.797 --> 09:01.164
Do you have friends?
Who do you talk to?

09:01.198 --> 09:02.465
Mostly Eugene.

09:02.500 --> 09:04.167
Who's that?
Mimsy's husband.

09:04.201 --> 09:05.168
Oh.

09:05.202 --> 09:06.469
<i>I really enjoy
talking to him.</i>

09:06.504 --> 09:08.605
He is so smart.
I've learned so much

09:08.639 --> 09:10.307
about running the business
from talking to him.

09:10.341 --> 09:11.975
I've run a business.
You can talk to me.

09:12.009 --> 09:13.810
Yeah, but I have
adults to talk to.

09:15.313 --> 09:17.147
So where's our son
this morning?

09:17.181 --> 09:18.949
He's at daycare.
Why? You're home.

09:18.983 --> 09:22.218
I'm working.
Or I'm trying to work.
I have clients coming over.

09:22.253 --> 09:24.254
I have to go.
[beeps]

09:24.288 --> 09:26.122
[beeps]

09:26.157 --> 09:27.824
[engine starts]

09:27.858 --> 09:30.327
I do not want a friend.

09:30.361 --> 09:31.928
Well, you're gonna
get a friend.

09:31.963 --> 09:33.296
So am I.

09:38.769 --> 09:40.370
Oh. Ricky. Hi.

09:40.404 --> 09:43.106
I just went to your office,
but some foreign guy
was in there.

09:43.140 --> 09:45.175
"Foreign"?
Well, a guy who wasn't you.

09:45.209 --> 09:48.612
Malkovich. He's overseeing
home schooling students.

09:48.646 --> 09:50.447
We can kick him out.
Come on.

09:50.481 --> 09:52.515
He can't still be talking
to Ashley.

09:52.550 --> 09:54.784
What do you want?
Why can't you just tell me
what it is right here?

09:54.819 --> 09:56.720
It's nothing bad.
I just wanna make sure

09:56.754 --> 09:58.722
you get your
college applications in.

09:58.756 --> 10:00.490
I saw that you hadn't
applied anywhere.

10:00.524 --> 10:02.492
I know that
I'm not gonna apply anywhere.

10:02.526 --> 10:04.361
But you're graduating,

10:04.395 --> 10:06.763
and you have an extremely high
grade point average,

10:06.797 --> 10:09.265
and your SATs were outstanding.

10:09.300 --> 10:12.969
If you aren't going to college,
why did you take the SATs?

10:13.004 --> 10:15.071
Because there were girls there.
Smart girls.

10:15.106 --> 10:18.074
I like smart girls.
And these weren't just
girls from this school.

10:18.109 --> 10:21.344
They were from all over.
And that was before Amy
and I started dating.

10:21.379 --> 10:24.014
Whatever your purpose was,
it doesn't matter.

10:24.048 --> 10:25.582
Well, it matters.

10:25.616 --> 10:27.250
But you're bright,

10:27.284 --> 10:29.285
and you aced your test,

10:29.320 --> 10:31.287
and you could
get into college.

10:31.322 --> 10:34.691
Maybe even get
financial assistance
or a scholarship, so--

10:34.725 --> 10:36.559
So I'm not going.

10:36.594 --> 10:39.562
I'm gonna stay
at the butcher ship
and see where I get with that.

10:39.597 --> 10:42.265
Don't you think
studying business could
get you somewhere with that?

10:42.299 --> 10:43.433
No.

10:43.467 --> 10:45.769
Well, I would still
encourage you

10:45.803 --> 10:47.937
to apply
to a couple of schools

10:47.972 --> 10:49.673
just in case
you change your mind

10:49.707 --> 10:51.474
I've never thought
about going to college,

10:51.509 --> 10:53.243
so I'm not
gonna change my mind.

10:53.277 --> 10:55.245
I have nothing
to change my mind about.

10:55.279 --> 10:56.913
Amy wants to go to college.

10:56.947 --> 10:58.648
I'm gonna work
and help her with John.

10:58.683 --> 11:00.350
She can be the one
who goes to college.

11:00.384 --> 11:03.119
Well, sounds very couple-ish.

11:03.154 --> 11:05.055
So you did decide
to get married.

11:05.089 --> 11:06.990
No, I did not decide
to get married.

11:07.024 --> 11:09.059
I said, "We'll see."

11:13.698 --> 11:16.833
Well, look who's standing
out in the hallway
all by himself.

11:16.867 --> 11:19.269
You are so
[exhales forcefully]

11:19.303 --> 11:20.804
going to have a baby.

11:20.838 --> 11:23.306
[chuckles]
Yep.

11:23.340 --> 11:26.710
And soon I will be so married
and living with Ben.

11:26.744 --> 11:29.646
Yeah. Well, uh...

11:29.680 --> 11:30.880
You don't wanna get married.

11:30.915 --> 11:32.348
I don't know, Adrian.

11:32.383 --> 11:33.850
I just think I'm too young.

11:33.884 --> 11:36.319
You know, I'm too young,
Amy's too young,

11:36.353 --> 11:38.254
Ben's too young,
you're too young.

11:38.289 --> 11:40.490
We're all too young
to be getting married
and having babies.

11:40.524 --> 11:44.260
Oh, yeah. But, hey,
that's what is.

11:44.295 --> 11:46.196
We're having babies.

11:46.230 --> 11:48.498
Or we had babies, and...

11:48.532 --> 11:51.701
Well, it's nice if there's both
a mommy and a daddy
to raise a baby, so--

11:51.736 --> 11:54.571
So the mommy and daddy
don't have to be married.

11:54.605 --> 11:58.007
I mean, I'm doing everything
I can for John,
and I'm not married to Amy.

11:58.042 --> 12:01.311
I wouldn't do
anything more for him
if I were married to Amy.

12:01.345 --> 12:05.014
I care about her.
I really care about her
and about John,

12:05.049 --> 12:08.351
but...I don't get marriage.

12:08.385 --> 12:11.254
Making a lifetime commitment
at our age

