27:11.626 --> 27:13.928
Just one more minute.
We're going.

27:17.265 --> 27:19.066
[beeping]

27:20.235 --> 27:22.236
[phone ringing]

27:23.638 --> 27:25.239
I'm sorry.

27:25.273 --> 27:26.907
Hi. Guess where I am.

27:26.942 --> 27:30.444
Not here. And Ashley
and her new study buddy
just got here.

27:30.479 --> 27:33.914
Oh, rats. All right.
I'll head that way, shortly.

27:33.949 --> 27:36.584
I'm going over to Ricky's.
I'll call you lar.

27:36.618 --> 27:38.853
Oh, I didn't guess
where you are.
You wanna tell me?

27:38.887 --> 27:40.354
Out with
your future mother-in-law.

27:40.389 --> 27:42.023
Who?
Nora.

27:42.057 --> 27:44.258
We're getting
a bite to eat at Jeff's.
It's a date.

27:45.427 --> 27:47.661
O-kay.
Don't worry about Ashley.

27:47.696 --> 27:50.431
She'll be fine. The counselor
and the teacher know this kid,
and I talked to his parents.

27:50.465 --> 27:53.300
All right. Well, uh,
enjoy your dinner.

27:53.335 --> 27:54.301
Okay. Bye.

27:54.336 --> 27:56.037
Just the kids
checking on me.

27:56.071 --> 27:57.438
Oh, that's sweet.

27:57.472 --> 27:59.173
So, where were we?

27:59.207 --> 28:01.208
You think Ricky and Amy
will get married?

28:02.244 --> 28:03.577
I don't know.

28:03.612 --> 28:05.046
You want them
to get married?

28:05.080 --> 28:06.447
Sure, if it means
we can hang out more.

28:06.481 --> 28:08.616
[chuckles]
Oh, George.

28:08.650 --> 28:10.618
I love hanging out
with you, too,

28:10.652 --> 28:12.653
but there's something
I've really gotta tell you.

28:13.822 --> 28:15.289
Oh, my God.

28:15.323 --> 28:17.625
That's Adrian's dad,
Ruben.

28:17.659 --> 28:18.926
He's not with his wife.

28:18.960 --> 28:21.328
Ow. Somebody's
gonna get in trouble.

28:30.105 --> 28:31.906
What are you
doing here? Hi.

28:31.940 --> 28:34.475
Nothing. Just grabbing
a bite after work.

28:34.509 --> 28:35.810
What are you doing here?

28:35.844 --> 28:37.244
Business.
We're working on a case.

28:37.279 --> 28:38.746
[Nora]
Ah.

28:38.780 --> 28:39.947
Mmm.

28:39.981 --> 28:41.882
Mmm.

28:44.586 --> 28:45.920
[chuckles]

28:47.689 --> 28:50.958
[together]
I'd like you to meet
my girlfriend.

28:52.494 --> 28:54.895
George, this is Ollie.

28:54.930 --> 28:57.598
Ollie, this is George.
Uh, Ricky's girlfriend's dad.

28:57.632 --> 28:59.567
Oh, George.
I've heard a lot about you.

29:00.936 --> 29:02.670
I was going to tell you.

29:02.704 --> 29:04.338
My God,

29:04.372 --> 29:06.107
I almost slept
with a lesbian.

29:06.141 --> 29:07.608
No, you didn't.

29:07.642 --> 29:10.411
Honey, this is Ruben.
Ruben is the guy--

29:10.445 --> 29:12.113
Who got me out. Ruben!
Yes.

29:12.147 --> 29:13.948
Oh, God, you're cute.
I love you.
[chuckling]

29:13.982 --> 29:15.583
How can I ever
thank you enough?

29:15.617 --> 29:17.651
Well, I just set things
in motion.

29:17.686 --> 29:19.153
Really, I didn't do anything.

29:19.187 --> 29:21.155
Besides, Ollie here
owes me dinner.

29:21.189 --> 29:22.756
She just beat me up in court.

29:22.791 --> 29:25.092
Oh, no. You know what?
I just got my first paycheck.

29:25.127 --> 29:27.061
I'm going to buy
everyone dinner here.

29:27.095 --> 29:29.063
No, Nora.
That's really sweet,
honey, but--

29:29.097 --> 29:30.531
No, but nothing.
I'm gonna do it.

29:30.565 --> 29:32.066
Come on.

29:36.571 --> 29:38.172
Yes, I knew
they were dating.

29:38.206 --> 29:39.874
I didn't know
you two were dating.

29:42.978 --> 29:44.945
We'll all
just have the soup.

29:44.980 --> 29:47.681
Yeah. Soup.
Yeah.

29:49.151 --> 29:50.718
[Nora]
Mmm.

29:53.488 --> 29:56.357
And you don't know
what the utilities are?

29:56.391 --> 29:58.692
No one's actually
lived here yet.

29:58.727 --> 30:00.694
The owners partially
furnished the place,

30:00.729 --> 30:02.496
and in the process
got into an argument,

30:02.531 --> 30:04.798
and split up before
ever taking possession.

30:04.833 --> 30:06.867
Aw, jeez. You should've
told us that first.

30:06.902 --> 30:09.270
This place has bad Karma
written all over it.

30:09.304 --> 30:11.639
I'm sure their Karma
followed them

30:11.673 --> 30:13.574
to their own
separate apartments, and...

30:13.608 --> 30:15.576
Come on, Ben.

30:15.610 --> 30:17.811
Adrian likes it.

30:17.846 --> 30:19.547
Your dad thinks
it's a good investment.

30:21.016 --> 30:22.349
Then we should just buy it?

30:22.384 --> 30:25.686
You're not buying anything.
I am.

30:25.720 --> 30:28.189
What the heck
is wrong with you?

30:28.223 --> 30:29.924
You made a checklist.

30:29.958 --> 30:32.359
This has everything
on your checklist.

30:32.394 --> 30:34.061
Yeah. Two bedrooms,
two bathrooms,

30:34.095 --> 30:37.331
black and white tile,
separate laundry
off the kitchen,

30:37.365 --> 30:39.767
electric stove,
white appliances,

30:39.801 --> 30:42.403
an outdoor space,
hardwood floors,

30:42.437 --> 30:44.004
et cetera, et cetera,

30:44.039 --> 30:46.407
and it is in
your price range.

30:46.441 --> 30:47.908
Is the paint zero VOC?

30:49.211 --> 30:50.444
Yes.

30:50.478 --> 30:52.947
Who the hell are you?

30:52.981 --> 30:55.249
This place is perfect
for the two of you.

30:55.283 --> 30:57.318
Could Ben and I
just hang out in here

30:57.352 --> 30:58.986
for, like,
a half hour or so?

30:59.020 --> 31:00.754
You know, kind of get
a feel for the place.

31:00.789 --> 31:02.923
I don't think
we need to do that.
Do that.

31:02.958 --> 31:04.391
I'll have Mike drop me off,

31:04.426 --> 31:06.860
and then he'll swing back by
and pick up the two of you.

31:06.895 --> 31:08.862
Can you close the door?
It locks automatically.

31:08.897 --> 31:12.266
Which means we could easily
lock ourselves out
and leave the baby inside.

31:12.300 --> 31:15.603
It's the temporary lock
so Realtors can show the condo.

31:16.838 --> 31:18.606
Good night.

31:25.580 --> 31:27.948
I know what you're gonna say--
that you love the place.

31:27.983 --> 31:29.483
But you've loved every place
we've seen,

31:29.517 --> 31:32.052
and I really just think
we have to keep looking.

31:34.522 --> 31:36.156
I do love it.

31:36.191 --> 31:37.925
I really do. I--

31:37.959 --> 31:41.128
I love the kitchen
and the location.

31:41.162 --> 31:44.531
But, mostly, Ben,
I love you.

31:44.566 --> 31:46.433
I love you, too, Adrian.

31:46.468 --> 31:49.136
Is there some reason
why you don't wanna leave home?

31:49.170 --> 31:51.538
I mean, are you afraid
that you and I can't handle

31:51.573 --> 31:53.607
raising a baby on our own?

31:53.642 --> 31:55.809
Because, Ben, we're still
gonna have plenty of help

31:55.844 --> 31:58.145
from our parents
and our friends, and...

31:58.179 --> 32:00.681
Well, I think
we're gonna be fine.

32:00.715 --> 32:02.683
I mean,
it's going to be crazy,

32:02.717 --> 32:04.985
but it's gonna be crazy
in a good way.

32:05.020 --> 32:06.320
You know,
we're very lucky.

32:06.354 --> 32:08.822
I know. I just...

32:08.857 --> 32:11.659
I don't think
that this is the place.

32:13.461 --> 32:16.263
Well, are you going to think
that any place

32:16.298 --> 32:19.333
is the right place
besides your own home?

32:20.568 --> 32:24.605
Okay. Your mom died
at that house.

32:24.639 --> 32:26.640
And you and your mom
and your dad

32:26.675 --> 32:28.575
were happy
in that house, and--

32:28.610 --> 32:30.144
Well, I'm sure
you always pictured yourself

32:30.178 --> 32:31.779
growing up at that house
and never leaving.

32:33.214 --> 32:35.516
But if you think about it,

32:35.550 --> 32:37.751
you were going to leave it.

32:37.786 --> 32:39.753
I mean, you were probably
gonna leave it next year

32:39.788 --> 32:43.057
after you graduated
from high school
and went to college.

32:43.091 --> 32:44.391
But I'd go back.

32:44.426 --> 32:45.893
Yeah, you would.

32:45.927 --> 32:47.828
I'm sure you'll always
go back to that house.

32:47.862 --> 32:49.863
It's like your safety zone

32:49.898 --> 32:51.665
where you can
hang on to things

32:51.700 --> 32:53.667
the way they were
supposed to be.

32:53.702 --> 32:55.703
The way things were
when your mom was there.

32:57.172 --> 32:59.606
I'm sure you have
some really wonderful memories

32:59.641 --> 33:02.176
of the three of you
in that house.

33:02.210 --> 33:04.144
Ben, those memories

33:04.179 --> 33:06.080
are gonna be with you
wherever you go.

33:06.114 --> 33:07.848
Even if the house went away,

33:07.882 --> 33:10.751
the memories
would still be with you.

33:10.785 --> 33:13.253
You can't hold
the memories in your hand.

33:13.288 --> 33:17.358
But those memories
are the real part of life,

33:17.392 --> 33:18.859
not the house.

33:18.893 --> 33:21.161
I always knew that you
were smarter than I am.

33:21.196 --> 33:22.863
Maybe just older and wiser.

33:22.897 --> 33:25.432
Just a year older
and a year wiser,

33:25.467 --> 33:28.268
but I'll catch up to you.

33:28.303 --> 33:29.803
Promise.

33:40.715 --> 33:41.682
[knocks]

33:41.716 --> 33:43.217
[Amy]
We're here.

33:49.224 --> 33:51.692
Hey, buddy.

33:51.726 --> 33:53.093
Thanks for bringing him.

33:53.128 --> 33:55.796
Yeah. I was happy to.

33:56.865 --> 33:58.832
I made you some dinner.

33:58.867 --> 34:01.201
If you don't want it tonight,
you can save it for tomorrow.

34:01.236 --> 34:03.303
It's just pasta and a salad.
What kind of pasta?

34:03.338 --> 34:05.472
Just spaghetti and meat sauce.

34:05.507 --> 34:08.708
So you boys have a great time.
I'll see you Sunday, John.

34:09.911 --> 34:12.045
You made me spaghetti
and meat sauce?

34:12.080 --> 34:14.047
You think you're gonna bribe me
with my favorite meal?

34:14.081 --> 34:16.116
Oh, I forgot it was
your favorite meal.

34:16.150 --> 34:17.684
It was just
the easiest thing to make.

34:17.719 --> 34:19.853
And since my dad wasn't home,
I thought I would make dinner.

34:19.888 --> 34:21.321
Uh-huh. Go on.

34:21.356 --> 34:26.025
As it turns out,
he thinks he's on a date
with your mom.

34:26.060 --> 34:29.295
Yeah. And Ashley and her friend
are doing their own thing.

34:29.330 --> 34:31.264
So there you go.
Spaghetti and meat sauce.

34:31.299 --> 34:33.233
Wait. Ashley has a friend?
New study buddy.

34:35.469 --> 34:38.071
So, I'll be going now.
Did you eat?

34:38.106 --> 34:40.674
No. That's okay.
I saved some of that
for myself at home. I'm fine.

34:40.708 --> 34:42.543
You're not going
to the football game
with Madison and Lauren?

34:42.577 --> 34:46.013
No. I'm just gonna have dinner
and have some time to myself.
It'll be nice.

34:46.047 --> 34:49.283
All right. Well,
you're welcome to come in
and eat, if you want.

34:49.317 --> 34:51.851
I haven't eaten.
No. It's okay.

34:51.886 --> 34:55.054
I think I may have
overstepped the boundaries
when I was here last weekend.

34:55.089 --> 34:56.623
Yeah, maybe.

34:56.658 --> 34:59.293
So I withdraw
my proposal of marriage.

35:00.628 --> 35:03.230
But I'm still open to having sex
when the time is right.

35:03.264 --> 35:05.866
Just come on in.
We'll have some dinner together.

35:05.900 --> 35:08.001
Okay. But after that,

35:08.036 --> 35:10.904
I'm leaving so you can have
your time with John.

35:23.663 --> 35:25.164
So?

35:25.198 --> 35:26.432
So?

35:26.466 --> 35:28.701
So come on.
What do you think?

35:28.735 --> 35:32.004
About the pizza?
Pizza's great.

35:34.874 --> 35:37.910
Okay, I--
I do have one regret.

35:37.944 --> 35:40.512
And what's that?
I regret that we wasted

35:40.547 --> 35:42.648
the whole summer
not having sex.

35:42.682 --> 35:45.217
Oh, good.
So you liked it.

35:45.252 --> 35:47.419
I liked it.

35:47.454 --> 35:49.355
I really liked it.

35:49.389 --> 35:50.990
I just wish
we'd done it sooner.

35:51.024 --> 35:52.925
Nah, I think it's good
we waited the three months.

35:52.959 --> 35:54.226
Four months.

35:54.261 --> 35:55.594
Whatever.

35:55.629 --> 35:57.730
It seemed like an eternity.

35:57.764 --> 35:59.865
But at this point,
we knew each other well enough

35:59.899 --> 36:02.001
that we were both
totally comfortable.

36:02.035 --> 36:04.903
Weren't we?
We were.

36:04.938 --> 36:08.107
Although I was a bit more
than comfortable.

36:08.141 --> 36:10.042
Yeah, you were.

36:10.076 --> 36:13.279
You know, I know we're just
juniors in high school,

36:13.313 --> 36:16.181
and this probably
isn't gonna last forever,

36:16.216 --> 36:18.751
but right now, right--

36:18.785 --> 36:20.819
right in this moment,

36:20.854 --> 36:22.788
I'm really happy.

36:22.822 --> 36:24.189
Me, too.

36:24.224 --> 36:26.992
[chuckles]

36:27.027 --> 36:29.228
I hope this won't
destroy your happiness,

36:29.262 --> 36:31.530
but I just have to say it.

36:32.932 --> 36:34.867
I love you, Grace.

36:34.901 --> 36:36.702
You sure?

36:36.736 --> 36:37.970
Yeah.

36:38.004 --> 36:41.740
Good. I love you, too.

36:44.678 --> 36:46.812
I love this feeling.
I love it.

36:46.846 --> 36:50.449
I love being with you.
I love having a boyfriend.

36:50.483 --> 36:52.251
I love having sex.

36:54.888 --> 36:57.723
Well, let's make
a promise to each other.

36:58.925 --> 37:02.394
If either one of us
doesn't feel this way--

37:02.429 --> 37:04.930
you know,
if we fall out of love--

37:05.865 --> 37:08.400
let's be really nice about it,

37:09.703 --> 37:13.272
because to lose this
would be really painful.

37:18.678 --> 37:20.879
I don't wanna worry
about that right now.

37:22.782 --> 37:24.683
But I completely agree.

37:24.718 --> 37:26.285
And who knows?

37:26.319 --> 37:27.886
Maybe it will work out.

37:27.921 --> 37:30.189
Maybe we'll be that couple
that meets in high school

37:30.223 --> 37:32.191
and stays together
through college

37:32.225 --> 37:35.060
and gets married
and has children
and grandchildren.

37:35.095 --> 37:36.862
I didn't know
guys thought like that.

37:36.896 --> 37:38.664
I was also thinking
about doing it again.

37:38.698 --> 37:41.600
[chuckles]
Me, too.

37:41.634 --> 37:43.435
I didn't know
girls thought like that.

37:43.470 --> 37:44.770
Yeah.

37:44.804 --> 37:46.305
[chuckles]

37:46.339 --> 37:49.708
[Madison]
Yeah, so, we're just gonna
wait a little longer.

37:49.743 --> 37:52.745
You know, and Jack's just
gonna have to go without sex.

37:52.779 --> 37:54.613
He can go without sex.
So can I.

37:54.647 --> 37:56.181
So can I.

37:56.216 --> 37:58.650
And in another year,
we'll be looking at colleges

37:58.685 --> 38:00.919
and deciding
where we wanna go

38:00.954 --> 38:02.988
and what we wanna
major in.

38:03.022 --> 38:05.691
As much as I hate him
for breaking up with me,

38:05.725 --> 38:07.693
I think Jesse
did the right thing.

38:07.727 --> 38:09.661
Yeah, I guess.

38:09.696 --> 38:12.231
I-- I kind of felt like
you guys really liked
each other, though.

38:12.265 --> 38:13.932
Yeah.

38:17.170 --> 38:19.271
Hey, Madison.

38:19.305 --> 38:20.305
Hey.

38:20.340 --> 38:22.474
Hey, Lauren.

38:22.509 --> 38:24.009
Hey, Jesse.

38:24.043 --> 38:25.444
How are you?

38:25.478 --> 38:27.813
I'm good. You?

38:27.847 --> 38:29.148
Good.

38:30.517 --> 38:32.384
Good night.

38:32.419 --> 38:34.420
Hey. Sorry that
took so long.

38:34.454 --> 38:36.121
No problem.

38:36.156 --> 38:38.590
Let's go eat.
I'm starving.
Okay.

38:49.202 --> 38:50.335
[door opens]

38:53.640 --> 38:55.674
That guy better not be here
at this time of night.

38:55.708 --> 38:57.843
What time of night?
Bedtime at night.

38:57.877 --> 38:59.645
He's not.

38:59.679 --> 39:01.313
Was that a...

39:01.347 --> 39:02.781
It's late.
You're seeing things.

39:02.816 --> 39:04.683
It's not that late.
What'd you do tonight?

39:04.717 --> 39:06.018
I had a date
with Ricky's mother.

39:06.052 --> 39:08.187
Oh? The married one
or the gay one?

39:08.221 --> 39:09.588
Did everyone know but me?

39:09.622 --> 39:12.124
I think so.
Good night.

39:23.069 --> 39:25.471
Ahh!
[phone beeping]

39:26.339 --> 39:27.272
<i>[line ringing]</i>

39:27.307 --> 39:28.340
<i>[Anne]
Hey.</i>

39:28.374 --> 39:30.075
I thought you might call.
Why is that?

39:30.109 --> 39:32.311
Have you talked to Amy?
No, not for hours. Why?

39:32.345 --> 39:34.379
So she hasn't
told you anything?

39:34.414 --> 39:36.548
No. She didn't even tell me
that Ricky's mom is gay.

39:36.583 --> 39:38.417
Yeah, she is.
Did everyone know but me?

39:38.451 --> 39:40.085
[chuckling]
Probably.

39:40.119 --> 39:42.221
[sighs]
So what's going on with Amy?
What now?

39:42.255 --> 39:43.989
What comes after
a ridiculous marriage proposal

39:44.023 --> 39:46.124
and trying to seduce
the father of her baby
in front of me?

39:46.159 --> 39:49.061
She wants to move in with him.
She wants to live with Ricky,
not married.

39:49.095 --> 39:52.097
What the hell?
She's not gonna do that.
I do not want her doing that.

39:52.131 --> 39:54.633
What is wrong with these people?
Getting married
and having babies

39:54.667 --> 39:56.535
and living with each other
and acting like total idiots.

39:56.569 --> 39:57.569
Jealous?

39:57.604 --> 39:59.605
Maybe.
But that doesn't mean my Amy

39:59.639 --> 40:01.240
is moving in with that--
that-- that--

40:01.274 --> 40:03.175
Father of her baby?

40:03.209 --> 40:04.877
I think it might be okay.

40:04.911 --> 40:06.645
I think it might
be good for them.

40:06.679 --> 40:08.647
You know, maybe by the time
she gets out of high school,

40:08.681 --> 40:10.716
she'll realize that
she doesn't wanna be married,

40:10.750 --> 40:12.551
and she'll choose
what college she goes to

40:12.585 --> 40:13.952
based on what's best
for her future

40:13.987 --> 40:15.420
and not what's closest
to the butcher shop.

40:15.455 --> 40:17.022
Anne, we are not
gonna let her do that.

40:17.056 --> 40:19.458
I don't really think
that we can stop her
from doing that,

40:19.492 --> 40:21.460
if that's what she wants to do,
and I'd rather not try.

40:21.494 --> 40:23.328
I'm supposed to just sit here
and let that happen?

40:23.363 --> 40:25.330
No. You're supposed
to get back out there

40:25.365 --> 40:27.566
and get a life,
and so am I.

40:27.600 --> 40:29.535
[sighs]

40:34.007 --> 40:37.409
Oh, I'm so sleepy.

40:38.411 --> 40:40.546
You wanna stay over?
[chuckles]

40:40.580 --> 40:43.215
I wanna stay over
for the rest of our lives,

40:43.249 --> 40:45.851
but I know
you don't want that,

40:45.885 --> 40:48.954
so I better get up
and go home.

40:48.988 --> 40:50.956
It's late.
You don't have to go.

40:50.990 --> 40:54.660
I wouldn't want you to feel
like I'm moving in or anything.

40:54.694 --> 40:57.796
Amy, I'd be okay with that--
with you and me living together.

40:57.830 --> 41:00.198
I'm just not okay
with getting married.

41:00.233 --> 41:01.833
You'd be okay with that?

41:01.868 --> 41:04.069
Oh. Oh, now I get it.

41:04.103 --> 41:06.538
